{
  "texts": [
    "4 | Example of a widely popular image database used for ANNs training and test, and how they are feed to the network.",
    "a Samples of the MNIST dataset of handwritten numeric digits considered in this article.",
    "In all cases images are represented in 28 × 28 px.",
    "Pixel brightness (or intensity) is codified in 256 levels ranging from 0 (fully OFF, black) to 1 (fully ON, white).",
    "b Readability loss as the resolution decreases from 28 × 28 pixels (case I) to 8 × 8 (case IV)."
  ]
}